class Solution {
    public boolean makeStringsEqual(String s, String target) {
        boolean hasOneS = false, hasOneTarget = false;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') {
                hasOneS = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        for (char c : target.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '1') {
                hasOneTarget = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        return hasOneS == hasOneTarget;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution checks if both strings have at least one '1'. If they do, or if neither do, it's possible to make s equal to target using the given operations. The presence or absence of '1' in both strings is the determining factor.
